lanterne (0.5.2) unstable; urgency=low
  * Modified the Strobe window to use a strobe period / duty cycle mechanism for timing; also, made the timing levels more conservative (for safety).

 -- John Pietrzak <jpietrzak8@gmail.com>  Sun, 02 Jun 2013 22:50:24 -0400

lanterne (0.5.1) unstable; urgency=low
  * Added the option to exit the app when the camera cover is closed.
  * Various tweaks to the UI, to make Lanterne a bit more usable as a general-purpose flashlight app.

 -- John Pietrzak <jpietrzak8@gmail.com>  Sat, 01 Jun 2013 20:00:59 -0400

lanterne (0.5.0) unstable; urgency=low
  * Added support for indicator LED.  On the preferences panel, the user can select to use the indicator LED for the torch, as well as select between seven levels of brightness for it.
  * The Torch On/Off button can now be used as a Morse Key (torch stays on for as long as you keep the button pressed).  This behavior can be controlled on the preferences panel.
  * Added the ability to use the camera button to control the torch.  (This is off by default, needs to be selected by the user on the preferences panel.)
  * Changed brightness level control on Strobe window to combo box, with more information about the actual brightness being chosen.

 -- John Pietrzak <jpietrzak8@gmail.com>  Fri, 31 May 2013 21:14:51 -0400

lanterne (0.4.0) unstable; urgency=low
  * Added check for camera cover status; Lanterne will now avoid turning LEDs on if cover is closed.  This check can be disabled from the new Preferences form (available from the drop-down menu).
  * Added ability to transmit Morse code text in a continuous loop.
  * Added option to run torch in a continuous pulse.

 -- John Pietrzak <jpietrzak8@gmail.com>  Thu, 30 May 2013 19:57:31 -0400

lanterne (0.3.0) unstable; urgency=low
  * Added ability to load text files for use in the morse code flasher.
  * Added a warning message about the brightness of the flash LEDs.  (Try not to look directly at them!)
  * Added ability to pause a running morse code transmission.
  * Added fix for rotation bug.

 -- John Pietrzak <jpietrzak8@gmail.com>  Wed, 29 May 2013 19:10:45 -0400

lanterne (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=low
  * Added new "Continuous SOS beacon" function.
  * Replaced "Torch" window with a simple on/off button.
  * Modified UI buttons to be more finger-friendly.
  * Added QSettings support for persistent storage of user parameters.
  * Modified Strobe timer to strobe first, not pause first.
  * Various improvements to package meta-data.

 -- John Pietrzak <jpietrzak8@gmail.com>  Tue, 28 May 2013 18:46:40 -0400

